{{Infobox philosopher | region = [[Western philosophy]] | era = [[20th-century philosophy]] | image = | caption = | name = John O'Neill | birth_date = | birth_place = | school_tradition = [[Marxism]], [[analytic philosophy]] | main_interests = [[Political philosophy]], [[Market (economics)|market]], [[ethics]], [[environmental philosophy]], [[ecological economics]] | notable_ideas = | influences = [[Karl Marx]], [[Otto Neurath]] | influenced = }}
'''John O'Neill''' is a [[philosopher]]. He is [[professor]] of [[Political Economy]] at the [[University of Manchester]].<ref name="um-fac bio" />
==Academic history== John O'Neill held the post of professor of philosophy at [[Lancaster University]].<ref name="um-fac bio" />
Previously, he was on the faculty of the [[University of Sussex]] and the [[University of Wales]].<ref name="um-fac bio" />
==Works== '''Books''' *{{cite book|last1=O'Neill|first1=John|first2=Andrew |last2=Light |first3=Alan |last3=Holland|title=Environmental Values|publisher=Routledge|location=London|year=2008}}<ref name="um-fac bio" /> *{{cite book|last=O'Neill|first=John|title=Markets, Deliberation and Environment|publisher=Routledge|location=London|year=2007}}<ref name="um-fac bio" /> *{{cite book|last=O'Neill|first=John|title=The Market: Ethics, Knowledge and Politics|publisher=Routledge|year=1998}}<ref name="um-fac bio" /> *{{cite book|title=Justice, Property and the Environment: Social and Legal Perspectives|editor1-last=Hayward |editor1-first=Time|year=1997 |editor2-last=O'Neill |editor2-first=John |location=Aldershot |publisher=Ashgate |series=Avebury Series in Philosophy}}<ref name="jaee-hughs97" />
