'''William Ralph Schroeder''' is an American philosopher and Emeritus Professor of [[Philosophy]] at the [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]]. He is known for his expertise on [[Continental Philosophy]] and [[Ethics]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Editors |first1=The |title=Simon Critchley & William Schroeder, A Companion to Continental Philosophy |journal=[[Journal of French and Francophone Philosophy]] |date=3 March 1997 |volume=9 |issue=1 |pages=76–76 |url=http://www.jffp.org/ojs/index.php/jffp/article/view/387/382 |accessdate=3 December 2018 |language=en |issn=2155-1162}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Groth |first1=Miles |title=A Companion to Continental Philosophy by Simon Critchley and William R. Schroeder (eds.). Oxford: Blackwell, 1998, pp. xv + 680, £65 or US$84.95 |journal=Philosophy |date=April 1999 |volume=74 |issue=2 |pages=282–295 |url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/philosophy/article/companion-to-continental-philosophy-by-simon-critchley-and-william-r-schroeder-eds-oxford-blackwell-1998-pp-xv-680-65-or-us8495/3173F16E0F6073C71D7C254B7CCD61D6 |accessdate=3 December 2018 |language=en |issn=1469-817X}}</ref> <ref>[http://www.philosophy.illinois.edu/people/ Faculty of Philosophy Department at the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]</ref><ref>William R. Schroeder: Continental Philosophy: A Critical Approach, Book Review by Marie Ramoya, ''[[Philosophia: International Journal of Philosophy]]'', 39 (1) (2010)</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Morris |first1=Phyllis S. |title=Sartre and his Predecessors: The Self and the Other, by William Ralph Schroeder |journal=Journal of the British Society for Phenomenology |date=January 1985 |volume=16 |issue=3 |pages=313–316 |doi=10.1080/00071773.1985.11007739 |url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00071773.1985.11007739 |accessdate=3 December 2018 |language=en |issn=0007-1773}}</ref> He has authored several books about philosophy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n82248988/ |title=Schroeder, William R. |publisher=worldcat.org |accessdate=July 8, 2016}}</ref>
